VirtNbrEvents.description: The number of times this virtual link has changed its state or an error has occurred.  Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system

VirtNbrHelloSuppressed.description: Indicates whether Hellos are being suppressed to the neighbor.

VirtNbrIpAddr.description: The IP address this virtual neighbor is using.

VirtNbrLsRetransQLen.description: The current length of the retransmission queue.

VirtNbrOptions.description: A bit mask corresponding to the neighbor's options field.  Bit 1

VirtNbrRestartHelperAge.description: Remaining time in current OSPF graceful restart interval

VirtNbrRestartHelperExitReason.description: Describes the outcome of the last attempt at acting as a graceful restart helper for the neighbor.

VirtNbrRestartHelperStatus.description: Indicates whether the router is acting as a graceful restart helper for the neighbor.

VirtNbrRtrId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the neighboring router in the Autonomous System.

VirtNbrState.description: The state of the virtual neighbor relationship.
